column4: Natural Sciences – SCI1 Utilize concepts – Students correctly apply, analyze, or evaluate information using discipline-specific facts and concepts.
column11: Advanced: Students correctly analyze, apply, and/or evaluate all, or nearly all, of the discipline-specific concepts measured.
column13: Proficient: Students correctly analyze, apply, and/or evaluate most of the discipline-specific concepts measured.
column15: Progressing: Students correctly analyze, apply, and/or evaluate some of the discipline-specific concepts measured.
column17: Beginning: Students correctly analyze, apply, and/or evaluate very few of the discipline-specific concepts measured.
column19: Unsatisfactory: Students do not analyze, apply, and/or evaluate the discipline-specific concepts measured.
